FSSO provides a single sign on solution to authenticate users transparently to a FortiGate
unit using credentials stored in Windows Active Directory.

environment when NTLM and Polling Mode are not used? (Select all that apply.)
A. An FSSO Collector Agent must be installed on every domain controller.
B. An FSSO Domain Controller Agent must be installed on every domain controller.
C. The FSSO Domain Controller Agent will regularly update user logon information on the
FortiGate unit.
D. The FSSO Collector Agent will retrieve user information from the Domain Controller
Agent and will send the user logon information to the FortiGate unit.
E. For non-domain computers, the only way to allow FSSO authentication is to install an
FSSO client.
Answer: B,D
